<br>
I follow the argument of both sides, though I think one has more of a leg to stand on.  I can see where each side is coming from, but something Syplh posted bothers me.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The total effect of our mistake was to make 3 guilds wait one week each, so what seems reasonable to me is for us to wait 3 weeks for our next KT.<br>
<br>
NB - TL - LoM - FK - VoF - LoL - BotS - SotE<br>
becomes<br>
NB - TL - LoM - VoF - LoL - BotS - FK - SotE<br>
and we skip the turn we took out of place<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If I am not mistaken you will get to kill him again before SotE gets to go?  I can't believe no one else has laid into you for that one.  Did someone say something about math geniuses?  Either that or I am reading that wrong because its not entirely clear.  The other way I see to interpret it is that you all will skip that turn when it comes and take it the next time around, which is more or less what everyone else is saying (before SotE or before NB is one guild difference, big deal).  I may have missed the boat entirely on that one too, happens often.<br>
<br>
I don't think you should be held to a different standard than anyone else, but you shouldn't be able to pick your standard.  There seem to be two precedents to go on and one is much more palatable than the other.  No one wants to be punished, thats why its a punishment.  To say you are sorry and you feel bad is good, I commend you for that.  I don't think it is a good standard though to let people off with a &quot;sorry, we screwed up&quot; though.  The Rathe is orderly for a reason and to let things go can create a slippery slope<br>
<br>
I think that with a change or lapse in rules some screw ups are bound to happen, but I personally would take extra caution in breaking form the norm by sending tells to double check.  Bottom line is that there needs to be something put in place by the RTA that is agreed upon ahead of time for address this.  That way if it happens its a non issue and the motives behind it are irrelevant.  Its hard to hold someone to a standard that wasn't officially in place.<br>
<br>
My opinion, for what its worth.<br>
<br>
-X <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elaundarnobillium>Elaundar Nobillium</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.stny.rr.com/drhager/sword.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toade, remember them?</span><br>  Posts: 324<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(1/1/03 12:13:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=238.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re</span><hr size=1> I'm bored, so I'll interject here (after all, Karadin indirectly invoked me with the Far Runners comment).  <br>
<br>
--------------<br>
Current Rotation Order:<br>
SotE - NB - TL - LoM - FK - VoF - LoL - BotS <br>
SotE - NB - TL - LoM - FK - VoF - LoL - BotS <br>
SotE - NB - TL - LoM - FK - VoF - LoL - BotS <br>
FK's rotation numbers are 5,13,21,29,...<br>
<br>
--------------<br>
FK jumped ahead of NB on this round which has caused the problems:<br>
SotE - FK - NB - TL - LoM - FK - VoF - LoL - BotS <br>
SotE - NB - TL - LoM - FK - VoF - LoL - BotS <br>
SotE - NB - TL - LoM - FK - VoF - LoL - BotS <br>
If nothing is done then FK's rotation numbers are 2,6,14,22,30,...<br>
<br>
I'm pretty sure everyone (including FK) agrees that this isn't acceptable.<br>
<br>
--------------<br>
Karadin's proposed to fix the situation by bumping FK before NB and skipping one rotation:<br>
SotE - FK - NB - TL - LoM - VoF - LoL - BotS <br>
SotE - NB - TL - LoM - VoF - LoL - BotS <br>
SotE - FK - NB - TL - LoM - VoF - LoL - BotS <br>
If this is done then FK's rotation numbers are 2,17,25,33<br>
<br>
When you look at the original order that means a 1 month punishment because they took a spawn 3 weeks early.  FK is opposed to this because on paper it looks like they are having to skip 2 entire rotations, when really they are only repaying in double what they accidentally took.  NB feels it is fair because it will discourage other guilds from taking spawns eariler than normal. <br>
<br>
--------------<br>
FK's counter-proposal is to leave the rotation as it is, but skip this rounds: <br>
SotE - FK - NB - TL - LoM - VoF - LoL - BotS <br>
SotE - NB - TL - LoM - FK - VoF - LoL - BotS <br>
SotE - NB - TL - LoM - FK - VoF - LoL - BotS <br>
Now FK's rotation numbers are 2,13,21,29, ...<br>
<br>
FK feels this is fair since it was accidental and NB is against it because they see it as no punishment at all.<br>
<br>
--------------<br>
Elaundar's counter-counter-proposal is to punish the number of rotation spots they skipped:<br>
SotE - FK - NB - TL - LoM - VoF - LoL - BotS <br>
SotE - NB - TL - LoM - VoF - LoL - BotS - FK<br>
SotE - NB - TL - LoM - VoF - LoL - BotS - FK<br>
With this, then FK rotation numbers are 2,16,24,32.  This is basically Sylph's comment, but is precise that they do not go before SotE on this round.<br>
<br>
In other words, FK illegally gained 3 positions so they should loose 3 positions. I really don't care what the punishment is that FK gets, but the it will establish the precidence.<br>
<br>
--------------<br>
